ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: In the next 30 days, to what extent do you intend to drink; women: 4 or more drinks, men: 5 or more drinks?
Notes: 1= I definitely will not; 7= I definitely will

ElementDescription: Over the next 30 days, how open are you to drinking; women: 4 or more drinks, men: 5 or more drinks?
Notes: 1= Not at all open; 7= Extremely open

ElementDescription: In the next 30 days, to what extent do you intend to drink; women: 8 or more drinks, men: 10 or more drinks?
Notes: 1= I definitely will not; 7= I definitely will

ElementDescription: Over the next 30 days, how open are you to drinking; women: 8 or more drinks, men: 10 or more drinks?
Notes: 1= Not at all open; 7= Extremely open

ElementDescription: In the next 30 days, to what extent do you intend to drink to point of having fuzzy memories or memories that become clear only after you are reminded later?
Notes: 1= I definitely will not; 7= I definitely will

ElementDescription: Over the next 30 days, how open are you to drinking to point of having fuzzy memories or memories that become clear only after you are reminded later?
Notes: 1= Not at all open; 7= Extremely open

ElementDescription: In the next 30 days, to what extent do you intend to drink to the point of blackout (being unable to remember, even after a reminder)?

ElementDescription: Over the next 30 days, how open are you to drinking to the point of blackout (being unable to remember, even after a reminder)?
Notes: 1= Not at all open; 7= Extremely open

ElementDescription: How intoxicated do you intend to get during this drinking episode?
Notes: 0 = Not at all intoxicated; 6 = Extremely intoxicated; 77 = No particular intention

ElementDescription: I intend to drink today.
Notes: 0= Strongly disagree; 4= Strongly agree

ElementDescription: Time at which participant submitted survey.
How likely is it that you will drink alcohol in the next 2 weeks?
Notes: 1 = Not at all likely; 2 = Somewhat likely; 3 = Very likely; 4 = Extremely likely

ElementDescription: How likely is it that you will get drunk from alcohol in the next 2 weeks?
Notes: 1 = Not at all likely; 2 = Somewhat likely; 3 = Very likely; 4 = Extremely likely

ElementDescription: How likely is it that you will consume 4 or more/5 or more drinks in one occasion within the next 2 weeks?
Notes: 1 = Not at all likely; 2 = Somewhat likely; 3 = Very likely; 4 = Extremely likely

ElementDescription: How likely is it that you will consume 8 or more/10 or more drinks in one occasion within the next two weeks?
Notes: 1 = Not at all likely; 2 = Somewhat likely; 3 = Very likely; 4 = Extremely likely

ElementDescription: I intend to consume 8 or more/10 or more drinks during this drinking event
Notes: 0= Strongly disagree; 4= Strongly agree

ElementDescription: I am open to drinking 8/10 or more standard drinks during this drinking episode
Notes: 0= Strongly disagree; 4= Strongly agree

ElementDescription: How likely is it that you will lose memory of drinking events as a result of alcohol use in the next 30 days?
Notes: Percent scale

ElementDescription: How likely is it that you will experience a blackout in the next 30 days?
Notes: Percent scale

ElementDescription: How likely is it that you will experience a brownout in the next 30 days?
Notes: Percent scale

ElementDescription: In the next three months, do you think you will drink alcohol beverages?
Notes: 0 = Definitely won''t; 1 = Probably won''t; 2 = Don''t know; 3 = Probably will; 4 = Definitely will

ElementDescription: In the next 30 days, do you think that you will drink alcoholic beverages?
Notes: 0 = Definitely won''t; 1 = Probably won''t; 2 = Don''t know; 3 = Probably will; 4 = Definitely will

ElementDescription: Do you think you will have an alcoholic beverage in the next twelve months?
Notes: 0 = Definitively yes; 1 = Maybe yes; 2 = Maybe no; 3 = Definitively no

ElementDescription: Do you think you will get drunk in the next twelve months?
Notes: 0 = Definitively yes; 1 = Maybe yes; 2 = Maybe no; 3 = Definitively no

Notes: 0 = Definitively yes; 1 = Maybe yes; 2 = Maybe no; 3 = Definitively no

ElementDescription: Do you think you will ever drink every month?
Notes: 0 = Definitively yes; 1 = Maybe yes; 2 = Maybe no; 3 = Definitively no

ElementDescription: If your best friend offered you a drink, would you drink it?
Notes: 0 = Definitively yes; 1 = Maybe yes; 2 = Maybe no; 3 = Definitively no

ElementDescription: If a relative (parent, sibling, aunt, uncle) offered you a drink, what would you do?
Notes: 0 = Definitively yes; 1 = Maybe yes; 2 = Maybe no; 3 = Definitively no

ElementDescription: Total Score of Partner Willingness to Change
Notes: Sum of chngruler1, chngruler2, chngruler3, chngruler4; 999 = Missing/NA

ElementDescription: Total Score of Self Willingness to Change
Notes: Sum of chngruler5, chngruler6, chngruler7; 999 = Missing/NA

ElementDescription: Total Willingness to Change Score
Notes: Sum of chngruler1 through chngruler7; 999 = Missing/NA
